---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy | The Taco Project" description="Read The Taco Project's privacy policy to understand how we collect, use, and protect your personal information.">
    <section class="bg-crema py-[100px] px-5">
        <div class="container">
            <h1 class="font-futura text-citrus text-[64px] lg:text-[96px] leading-[0.88] uppercase tracking-tight mb-12">Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.4] mb-8"><strong>Last Updated On:</strong> 23-Jan-2025</p>

            <div class="space-y-8">
                <section class="space-y-4">
                    <h2 class="font-futura text-ink text-[32px] leading-tight tracking-tight uppercase">Introduction</h2>
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">
                        Welcome to The Taco Project! We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring that your personal information is handled securely and responsibly. This Privacy Policy outlines the types of information we collect, how we collect it, the purposes for which we use it, and the measures we take to protect your data.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="space-y-4">
                    <h2 class="font-futura text-ink text-[32px] leading-tight tracking-tight uppercase">Types of Information Collected</h2>
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">We collect various types of personal information from our customers, including but not limited to:</p>
                    <ul class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6] list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                        <li>Name</li>
                        <li>Email address</li>
                        <li>Phone number</li>
                        <li>Mailing address</li>
                        <li>Order details (such as items purchased and payment method)</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="space-y-4">
                    <h2 class="font-futura text-ink text-[32px] leading-tight tracking-tight uppercase">Method of Information Collection</h2>
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">We collect customer data through various methods, including:</p>
                    <ul class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6] list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                        <li>Online forms and applications (e.g., order forms, newsletter sign-ups)</li>
                        <li>Phone calls, texts, and emails</li>
                        <li>In-person interactions at our restaurant or events</li>
                        <li>Website cookies and tracking technologies</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="space-y-4">
                    <h2 class="font-futura text-ink text-[32px] leading-tight tracking-tight uppercase">Purpose of Data Collection</h2>
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">The information we collect is used for the following purposes:</p>
                    <ul class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6] list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                        <li>To process and manage orders (online and in-store)</li>
                        <li>To improve and personalize customer experience</li>
                        <li>To communicate with customers regarding their orders, promotions, or events</li>
                        <li>To send marketing materials or newsletters, if subscribed</li>
                        <li>To comply with legal and regulatory requirements</li>
                        <li>To ensure the safety and security of our website and physical locations</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="space-y-4">
                    <h2 class="font-futura text-ink text-[32px] leading-tight tracking-tight uppercase">Data Security Measures</h2>
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">We implement a variety of security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, use, or disclosure. These measures include:</p>
                    <ul class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6] list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                        <li>Encryption of sensitive data</li>
                        <li>Secure payment processing systems</li>
                        <li>Access controls to limit who can access your information</li>
                        <li>Regular security assessments</li>
                        <li>Employee training on data protection practices</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="space-y-4">
                    <h2 class="font-futura text-ink text-[32px] leading-tight tracking-tight uppercase">Data Sharing</h2>
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal information to third parties. However, we may share your data with trusted third parties only under the following circumstances:</p>
                    <ul class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6] list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                        <li>To process and fulfill orders (e.g., payment processors, delivery services)</li>
                        <li>To comply with legal obligations or regulatory requirements</li>
                        <li>To protect the rights, property, or safety of The Taco Project, our customers, or others</li>
                        <li>With your explicit consent, for example, when subscribing to our newsletter or participating in promotions</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="space-y-4">
                    <h2 class="font-futura text-ink text-[32px] leading-tight tracking-tight uppercase">User Rights</h2>
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">
                        You have the right to access, update, or delete your personal information at any time. If you wish to exercise these rights or have any concerns regarding your data, please contact us using the information provided below.
                    </p>
                </section>

                <section class="space-y-4">
                    <h2 class="font-futura text-ink text-[32px] leading-tight tracking-tight uppercase">SMS Communications Policy</h2>
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">
                        <strong>SMS opt-in or phone numbers for the purpose of SMS are not being shared with any third party and affiliate company for marketing purposes.</strong>
                    </p>
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">
                        <strong>SMS Consent Communication:</strong> The information (Phone Numbers) obtained as part of the SMS consent process will not be shared with third parties for marketing purposes.
                    </p>
                    
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]"><strong>Types of SMS Communications:</strong></p>
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">If you have consented to receive text messages from The Taco Project, you may receive messages related to the following:</p>
                    <ul class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6] list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                        <li>Appointment reminders</li>
                        <li>Follow-up messages</li>
                        <li>Billing inquiries</li>
                        <li>Promotions or offers (if applicable)</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6] italic">
                        Example: "Hello, this is a friendly reminder of your upcoming catering order with The Taco Project on [Date] at [Time]. Reply STOP to opt out of SMS messaging at any time."
                    </p>

                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">
                        <strong>Message Frequency:</strong> Message frequency may vary depending on the type of communication. For example, you may receive up to 2 SMS messages per week related to your appointments or billing.
                    </p>

                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">
                        <strong>Potential Fees for SMS Messaging:</strong> Please note that standard message and data rates may apply, depending on your carrier's pricing plan. These fees may vary if the message is sent domestically or internationally.
                    </p>

                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]"><strong>Opt-In Method:</strong> You may opt-in to receive SMS messages from The Taco Project in the following ways:</p>
                    <ul class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6] list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                        <li>Verbally, during a conversation</li>
                        <li>By submitting an online form</li>
                        <li>By filling out a paper form</li>
                    </ul>

                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">
                        <strong>Opt-Out Method:</strong> You can opt out of receiving SMS messages at any time. To do so, simply reply "STOP" to any SMS message you receive. Alternatively, you can contact us directly to request removal from our messaging list.
                    </p>

                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">
                        <strong>Help:</strong> If you are experiencing any issues, you can reply with the keyword HELP. Or, you can get help directly from us at <a href="mailto:info@thetacoproject.com" class="text-hot-sauce hover:underline">info@thetacoproject.com</a>.
                    </p>

                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">
                        <strong>Additional Options:</strong> If you do not wish to receive SMS messages, you can choose not to check the SMS consent box on our forms.
                    </p>

                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]"><strong>Standard Messaging Disclosures:</strong></p>
                    <ul class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6] list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
                        <li>Message and data rates may apply.</li>
                        <li>You can opt-out at any time by texting "STOP."</li>
                        <li>For assistance, text "HELP" or visit our Privacy Policy and Terms and Conditions pages.</li>
                        <li>Message frequency may vary.</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="space-y-4">
                    <h2 class="font-futura text-ink text-[32px] leading-tight tracking-tight uppercase">Contact Information</h2>
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">
                        If you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy or how we handle your personal information, please contact us at:
                    </p>
                    <p class="font-geist text-ink text-sm leading-[1.6]">
                        <strong>The Taco Project</strong><br />
                        1086 N Broadway,<br />
                        Yonkers, NY 10701, United States of America<br />
                        <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:info@thetacoproject.com" class="text-hot-sauce hover:underline">info@thetacoproject.com</a><br />
                        <strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+19143754000" class="text-hot-sauce hover:underline">914-375-4000</a>
                    </p>
                </section>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
